<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1870-08-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1870-08-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="4" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d4">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">No. 4.</note>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Received at Washington August
                                22.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Jay</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Fish</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1870-08-21"><hi rend="smallcaps">August</hi> 21, 1870.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Fish,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Secretary, Washington:</hi></p>
                        <p>England, Italy, and Russia have mutually agreed to rest neutral, and not
                            to change their position without notice and statement of reasons.
                            Austria, asked to join neutral league, will consent with the additional
                            understanding that efforts for mediation shall be made, not separately
                            but jointly.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>JAY.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>